stylometry: @RISK replicates a model with different random numbers and reports summary measures. For example, @RISK can calcuate profit levels for different order quantities. Some of the generally useful information @RISK supplies the user with include the minimum, maximum, mean, and standard deviation values. When we were looking at the Walton Bookstore calendar order quantity simulation model, we chose the value with a high mean (the profit associated with the order quantity based on the min and max values) and a low standard deviation (which means the information is more reputable and less inclined to deviate from the result given by @RISK).
